# Implementation Plan - Google Sign-In Integration

This plan outlines the design and implementation details to add Google Sign-In to our MERN application using the modern Google Identity Services API (Google ID Token verification). It avoids using Passport.js or OAuth Authorization Code Flow, relying purely on verified Google ID tokens.

## Architecture & How Google Sign-In Works

Here is a summary of the authentication flow:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant Frontend as React App (@react-oauth/google)
    participant Google as Google Identity Services
    participant Backend as Node/Express API (google-auth-library)
    participant DB as MongoDB

    User->>Frontend: Clicks "Continue with Google"
    Frontend->>Google: Requests authentication
    Google->>User: Displays consent screen / account chooser
    User->>Google: Approves authentication
    Google->>Frontend: Returns Google ID Token (signed JWT)
    Frontend->>Backend: Sends Google ID Token (POST /api/auth/google)
    Note over Backend: Verifies ID Token using Google public keys
    Backend->>DB: Checks if email/googleId exists
    alt Account doesn't exist
        Backend->>DB: Creates user (no password, sets googleId)
    else Account exists via Email/Password
        Backend->>DB: Links Google ID to existing account
    else Account exists via Google
        Backend->>DB: Retrieves user details
    end
    Backend->>Backend: Generates Application's JWT session token
    Backend->>Frontend: Returns JWT token + User details
    Frontend->>Frontend: Stores JWT in document.cookie (matches normal sign-in)
    Frontend->>User: Redirects to Dashboard
```

