### 3. Frontend Updates

We will add the `@react-oauth/google` package and include a login button in our existing Sign In page.

#### Dependencies
We need to install `@react-oauth/google` in the client project:
```bash
npm install @react-oauth/google
```

#### [MODIFY] [main.tsx](file:///c:/web%20dev/mern%20stack/mern-auth/client/src/main.tsx)
- Wrap the app (or `<App />`) in `<GoogleOAuthProvider clientId={import.meta.env.VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID}>` to make Google Auth services available.

#### [MODIFY] [signIn.tsx](file:///c:/web%20dev/mern%20stack/mern-auth/client/src/pages/signIn.tsx)
- Import `GoogleLogin` from `@react-oauth/google`.
- Render the `GoogleLogin` button component inside the Sign In card.
- In the `onSuccess` callback:
  - Extract the Google `credential` (ID Token).
  - Send `POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/google` with `{ idToken: credential }`.
  - Store the application's returned session token in `document.cookie` (using the same logic as email/password sign-in).
  - Redirect the user to `/dashboard`.
- Handle any authorization failures.

